WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:17.330 --> 00:00:20.540
Did you know there's an awesome treasure at the end of this sea?!

3
00:00:20.540 --> 00:00:23.340
And whoever gets it becomes King of the Pirates!

4
00:00:23.340 --> 00:00:24.960
Isn't that exciting?!

5
00:00:24.960 --> 00:00:28.010
Cool new adventures are waiting out there!

6
00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:38.060
BON VOYAGE! Hitokakera no yuuki hirogete
BON VOYAGE! Light the ember of courage and let the fire grow

7
00:00:38.060 --> 00:00:45.660
Mirai he no SHIPPO chotto mieta yo
I caught a glimpse at what's beyond the horizon

8
00:00:45.780 --> 00:00:48.210
Back when we first started

9
00:00:45.780 --> 00:00:53.430
Saisho wa minna BARABARA ni egaite ita chiheisen

10
00:00:48.210 --> 00:00:53.430
we had separate ideas about where we would soon go

11
00:00:53.740 --> 00:00:55.380
Things have changed now,

12
00:00:53.740 --> 00:01:00.440
Ima nara hitotsu no bouenkyou de nozokeru

13
00:00:55.380 --> 00:01:00.440
when we look towards our dreams we all share one telescope

14
00:01:00.730 --> 00:01:05.680
When you find that your heart's been led astray

15
00:01:00.730 --> 00:01:09.980
Kimi no KOKORO madowasu unmei no shoppai KONPASU

16
00:01:05.680 --> 00:01:09.980
time to calibrate your compasses

17
00:01:09.980 --> 00:01:13.010
Sakate ni kaji toru yo
Set a new course, turn the tables now

18
00:01:13.010 --> 00:01:20.300
BON VOYAGE! SHIGARAMI mo kako mo sutete
BON VOYAGE! Shed your previous baggage, forget the past

19
00:01:20.300 --> 00:01:27.140
Bokura nara sore demo waraeteru hazu
Smiles can weather a storm, we know that better than anyone

20
00:01:27.140 --> 00:01:29.080
Don't you fret,

21
00:01:27.140 --> 00:01:34.900
Yume wo kanaeru tame no namida naraba

22
00:01:29.080 --> 00:01:34.900
tears shed along the way to your dreams are not in vain

23
00:01:34.900 --> 00:01:41.100
Oshiku wa nai PRECIOUS IN MY LIFE
You know that you're all PRECIOUS IN MY LIFE

24
00:01:42.060 --> 00:01:49.210
Mirai he no SHIPPO chotto mieta yo
I caught a glimpse at what's beyond the horizon

25
00:01:51.800 --> 00:01:56.470
Um, young lady...
May I call you Aisa?

26
00:01:56.470 --> 00:02:00.350
Can you really tell where
the Blue Sea folks' ship is headed?

27
00:02:00.350 --> 00:02:01.270
Yeah...

28
00:02:01.270 --> 00:02:03.520
What a mysterious power...

29
00:02:03.520 --> 00:02:08.020
Being able to hear people in
the forest from this far away...

30
00:02:08.020 --> 00:02:10.900
Anyway, are you all right?

31
00:02:10.900 --> 00:02:13.070
You've been trembling
for a while now.

32
00:02:14.410 --> 00:02:15.490
It's just...

33
00:02:16.070 --> 00:02:20.120
It's just that I've never
felt so afraid before.

34
00:02:20.120 --> 00:02:21.620
Everyone's voices...

35
00:02:22.120 --> 00:02:25.500
Everyone's voices keep
disappearing one after another...

36
00:02:28.750 --> 00:02:30.250
Yes, I'm sorry.

37
00:02:30.250 --> 00:02:33.090
Then we should hurry, Conis.

38
00:02:33.090 --> 00:02:34.430
Yes, Father.

39
00:02:37.550 --> 00:02:40.680
I've become a pirate at last!

40
00:02:40.680 --> 00:02:43.690
I think I'll look for the gold
instead of the others!

41
00:02:43.690 --> 00:02:45.020
I'll surprise them all!

42
00:02:48.770 --> 00:02:51.860
That place seems suspicious to me...

43
00:02:52.610 --> 00:02:53.740
Who knows?

44
00:02:54.490 --> 00:02:56.700
Maybe everyone is over there...

45
00:03:07.670 --> 00:03:12.510
Pirate Robin vs. Abbot Yama

46
00:03:12.510 --> 00:03:13.880
Hold on!

47
00:03:13.880 --> 00:03:15.470
You're leaving, weird knight?!

48
00:03:15.470 --> 00:03:17.840
My apologies, but I'm afraid
I must pursue Enel.

49
00:03:17.840 --> 00:03:20.640
What?! You're just gonna
leave a lady to fend for herself?!

50
00:03:20.640 --> 00:03:22.680
That is why I apologized.

51
00:03:23.350 --> 00:03:29.690
I don't have time to explain,
but my men's lives are at stake.

52
00:03:29.690 --> 00:03:30.730
Nay...

53
00:03:31.360 --> 00:03:33.360
this entire land may be at stake...

54
00:03:33.360 --> 00:03:34.860
Can you fly, Pierre?

55
00:03:36.070 --> 00:03:37.200
You can't be serious...

56
00:03:38.200 --> 00:03:40.200
Hey, I said wait!

57
00:03:40.200 --> 00:03:41.620
You heartless jerk!

58
00:03:41.620 --> 00:03:44.200
And you call yourself god?!

59
00:03:44.200 --> 00:03:47.790
Get back here! Think this through!

60
00:03:57.380 --> 00:04:00.390
I should get these two
patched up for now...

61
00:04:00.390 --> 00:04:02.810
You're both alive, right?!

62
00:04:03.390 --> 00:04:05.640
Come back soon, Chopper...

63
00:04:07.350 --> 00:04:08.730
Wh-What?! What was that?!

64
00:04:14.190 --> 00:04:16.940
Nami! Heso!

65
00:04:17.820 --> 00:04:18.650
Conis?!

66
00:04:21.320 --> 00:04:22.200
Heso!

67
00:04:22.830 --> 00:04:24.040
Mister!

68
00:04:24.620 --> 00:04:26.620
What are you doing here?

69
00:04:29.750 --> 00:04:31.830
Shut that horn off already!

70
00:04:34.000 --> 00:04:36.050
Let me go!

71
00:04:36.050 --> 00:04:38.010
Wait... No! You can't get off!

72
00:04:38.010 --> 00:04:39.260
Let me go!

73
00:04:39.260 --> 00:04:42.010
If you go any farther in,
you'll never get out alive!

74
00:04:42.010 --> 00:04:44.510
We agreed to leave right away!

75
00:04:44.510 --> 00:04:45.640
Let go!

76
00:04:45.010 --> 00:04:45.640
No!

77
00:04:45.640 --> 00:04:46.970
Who's that kid?

78
00:04:46.970 --> 00:04:48.980
Oh, this is Aisa...

79
00:04:48.980 --> 00:04:50.850
Back off, Blue Sea scum!

80
00:04:50.850 --> 00:04:52.230
I'll eliminate you!

81
00:04:52.230 --> 00:04:53.860
I'm a warrior of Shandora!

82
00:04:53.860 --> 00:04:57.490
So? You're gonna fight me?
Don't make me impact you.

83
00:04:57.490 --> 00:05:00.820
How awful! They're both charred
black! They need first aid, quick!

84
00:05:01.200 --> 00:05:02.820
Sorry to interrupt,

85
00:05:02.820 --> 00:05:05.330
but you should sail onto
the path we rode in on!

86
00:05:06.370 --> 00:05:09.290
It's a new river that
we created with a milky dial.

87
00:05:09.290 --> 00:05:12.790
If you follow it, you can exit
straight into the White-White Sea.

88
00:05:12.790 --> 00:05:14.090
Hurry, before we're seen...

89
00:05:14.540 --> 00:05:17.380
Shouldn't you have
come more quietly then?!

90
00:05:17.380 --> 00:05:21.380
Oh, yes. I also have
something for you.

91
00:06:07.350 --> 00:06:09.930
Oh, you're still at it?

92
00:06:21.320 --> 00:06:23.200
Sorry about that.

93
00:06:23.200 --> 00:06:25.280
I must've dozed off there.

94
00:06:25.280 --> 00:06:27.200
What's wrong?

95
00:06:27.620 --> 00:06:29.290
You seem to be in pain.

96
00:06:29.950 --> 00:06:34.620
Although, like I promised,
I haven't done anything...

97
00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:37.130
I...

98
00:06:39.380 --> 00:06:43.380
can't... beat you...?

99
00:06:46.970 --> 00:06:48.930
Yes, that's right.

100
00:06:50.560 --> 00:06:52.430
Now do you understand?

101
00:06:52.430 --> 00:06:54.980
I am lightning.

102
00:06:56.270 --> 00:07:00.570
How could a mere man
hope to defeat lightning?

103
00:07:01.280 --> 00:07:06.110
As a native of the sky, you've surely
seen distant lightning before.

104
00:07:06.110 --> 00:07:11.740
Since ancient times, men have supplanted
their fear of nature with the divine

105
00:07:11.740 --> 00:07:15.960
to flee from incomprehensible terror.

106
00:07:16.670 --> 00:07:20.590
They believe all supernatural
phenomena are acts of gods

107
00:07:20.590 --> 00:07:22.630
beyond their understanding.

108
00:07:25.470 --> 00:07:27.680
Those calamities from the heavens

109
00:07:27.680 --> 00:07:31.930
that made humanity
kneel in submission...

110
00:07:32.640 --> 00:07:34.310
They are me.

111
00:07:41.610 --> 00:07:44.070
Oh? A breath dial, huh?

112
00:07:44.900 --> 00:07:48.110
Burn Blade!

113
00:08:12.100 --> 00:08:13.850
I must tell Wyper!

114
00:08:13.850 --> 00:08:15.980
There's no point in fighting him!

115
00:08:17.640 --> 00:08:19.230
Wyper would only die in vain!

116
00:08:19.770 --> 00:08:22.900
Even if he risks his life,
a reject will have no effect!

117
00:08:23.650 --> 00:08:26.110
So now you choose to run?

118
00:08:26.650 --> 00:08:28.700
I need to retreat and think!

119
00:08:28.700 --> 00:08:30.030
At this rate...

120
00:08:30.030 --> 00:08:31.200
At this rate...!

121
00:08:37.870 --> 00:08:41.210
Did you think you could move
faster than lightning?

122
00:08:44.050 --> 00:08:46.510
Your five minutes are up.

123
00:08:47.670 --> 00:08:49.800
Now it's my turn.

124
00:08:57.140 --> 00:09:01.150
One Million Volts: Vari!

125
00:09:02.020 --> 00:09:06.980
Run Wyper!

126
00:09:31.880 --> 00:09:33.090
What was thaat?

127
00:09:39.180 --> 00:09:41.140
No!

128
00:09:41.640 --> 00:09:43.150
What?! What?!

129
00:09:43.150 --> 00:09:45.400
What's going on now?!

130
00:09:45.400 --> 00:09:46.770
What happened?!

131
00:09:46.770 --> 00:09:48.230
Their voices...

132
00:09:48.230 --> 00:09:50.150
are disappearing...!

133
00:09:57.950 --> 00:09:58.990
Pity...

134
00:09:58.990 --> 00:10:02.830
It seems the electricity traveled
along the milky road.

135
00:10:02.830 --> 00:10:06.460
Twenty voices disappeared
after that discharge.

136
00:10:07.090 --> 00:10:09.050
Fools...

137
00:10:13.180 --> 00:10:18.350
The eighty-one-man
Upper Yard survival game...

138
00:10:18.970 --> 00:10:21.600
Two hours have passed.

139
00:10:21.600 --> 00:10:25.650
Fifty-six have fallen.

140
00:10:26.810 --> 00:10:30.690
Thirteen of God's Army remain.

141
00:10:31.280 --> 00:10:35.200
Five Straw Hats remain.

142
00:10:36.780 --> 00:10:39.410
Seven Shandians remain.

143
00:10:40.660 --> 00:10:44.210
That makes for a total
of twenty-five left...

144
00:10:45.080 --> 00:10:47.710
That's more than I expected.

145
00:10:48.420 --> 00:10:49.840
No matter.

146
00:10:49.840 --> 00:10:52.630
I'll corner them all slowly but surely.

147
00:10:53.800 --> 00:10:58.260
Who will get to accompany
me in the end?

148
00:11:02.560 --> 00:11:04.060
Amazing!

149
00:11:04.060 --> 00:11:05.730
You're incredible, Nami!

150
00:11:08.110 --> 00:11:10.570
It's all yours now!

151
00:11:10.570 --> 00:11:12.400
Yeah, thanks!

152
00:11:13.400 --> 00:11:15.650
I love it!

153
00:11:15.650 --> 00:11:17.320
It's so much faster!

154
00:11:17.740 --> 00:11:21.620
Yes. Jet dials went extinct
hundreds of years ago,

155
00:11:21.620 --> 00:11:27.540
so I was shocked that the waver
you left with me had one onboard!

156
00:11:27.920 --> 00:11:31.670
But... what do we do now?

157
00:11:31.670 --> 00:11:36.300
We had planned to escort you all
to the edge of Skypiea, but...

158
00:11:36.300 --> 00:11:37.470
Yeah.

159
00:11:37.930 --> 00:11:41.600
For now, let's get the ship
to the rendezvous coast.

160
00:11:42.100 --> 00:11:44.520
I'm sure they're doing fine...

161
00:11:45.350 --> 00:11:48.730
Well, the four of them
together are unstoppable!

162
00:11:48.730 --> 00:11:50.940
There's no group of four on the island.

163
00:11:51.360 --> 00:11:52.110
Huh?

164
00:11:53.650 --> 00:11:55.740
At most, there are
two-person groups.

165
00:11:56.150 --> 00:11:59.910
If there were four people
moving together, I'd know!

166
00:12:00.410 --> 00:12:02.200
Mantra...

167
00:12:02.950 --> 00:12:05.620
The thing God and those priests use?

168
00:12:06.870 --> 00:12:10.250
I was born with it!

169
00:12:10.250 --> 00:12:11.880
That's why I'm afraid...

170
00:12:12.460 --> 00:12:16.550
You have no idea how scary
it is hearing voices disappear!

171
00:12:17.300 --> 00:12:19.180
Are you gonna cry again?

172
00:12:19.890 --> 00:12:22.430
I am not crying,
you stupid Blue Sea person!

173
00:12:23.470 --> 00:12:26.850
Her waver broke down,
and we passed by

174
00:12:26.850 --> 00:12:30.850
just as a sky shark
was about to attack her...

175
00:12:30.850 --> 00:12:32.650
What were you planning to do?!

176
00:12:33.070 --> 00:12:34.530
I don't know!

177
00:12:34.530 --> 00:12:37.360
But I can't just sit
around doing nothing!

178
00:12:40.740 --> 00:12:41.530
Raki...

179
00:12:42.070 --> 00:12:43.200
Everyone...

180
00:12:48.410 --> 00:12:51.420
I hope everyone's all right...

181
00:13:07.220 --> 00:13:10.440
Man, this is no good...

182
00:13:10.850 --> 00:13:16.650
My bag's outside, and there's
no fruit on all these rotting trees...

183
00:13:16.650 --> 00:13:19.990
I was really looking forward
to that breakfast...

184
00:13:20.860 --> 00:13:23.780
What a weird cave I wound up in.

185
00:13:23.780 --> 00:13:26.660
I can't find the exit anywhere...

186
00:13:27.660 --> 00:13:30.210
I wonder if everyone's
at the City of Gold by now.

187
00:13:30.210 --> 00:13:32.960
I bet it's pretty,
all made out of gold...

188
00:13:32.960 --> 00:13:38.630
That reminds me, I once heard
at a bar that gold stew tastes great...

189
00:13:51.190 --> 00:13:53.100
I've walked a long way.

190
00:13:54.060 --> 00:13:55.560
Guess I'll have that lunch...

191
00:14:00.280 --> 00:14:01.280
Who's there?!

192
00:14:07.280 --> 00:14:09.160
What's that supposed to mean?

193
00:14:09.160 --> 00:14:10.790
Don't tell me you're after my meal?!

194
00:14:10.790 --> 00:14:11.460
Huh?!

195
00:14:12.120 --> 00:14:13.080
Well, forget it!

196
00:14:14.330 --> 00:14:16.420
Quit staring at it!

197
00:14:26.350 --> 00:14:27.760
Stop following me!

198
00:14:29.140 --> 00:14:32.020
Listen! I already ate all my food!

199
00:14:32.020 --> 00:14:35.270
I don't have any more! Even if
I did, I wouldn't give you any!

200
00:14:35.270 --> 00:14:37.400
Got it?! Now get lost!

201
00:14:38.770 --> 00:14:41.150
And you're walking all weird.

202
00:14:41.150 --> 00:14:43.240
Which way are you even facing?!

203
00:14:44.740 --> 00:14:47.410
You wanna take me on?! Huh?!

204
00:14:50.450 --> 00:14:52.580
In three hours,

205
00:14:52.580 --> 00:14:56.880
out of the eighty-one
people on this island...

206
00:14:56.880 --> 00:14:58.670
five will remain.

207
00:14:58.670 --> 00:15:01.800
Only one hour left until
the time I proclaimed is up...

208
00:15:01.800 --> 00:15:03.550
Current number of survivors...

209
00:15:03.550 --> 00:15:05.470
is twenty-five.

210
00:15:08.050 --> 00:15:09.100
This can't be!

211
00:15:09.100 --> 00:15:11.930
What is God Enel doing here?!

212
00:15:11.930 --> 00:15:13.560
He's going down!

213
00:15:24.990 --> 00:15:28.370
Twenty-four left.

214
00:15:35.710 --> 00:15:37.000
Oh, my.

215
00:15:37.000 --> 00:15:40.290
You're nothing but talk, Missy...

216
00:15:42.920 --> 00:15:45.720
Stomach Mountain!

217
00:15:53.310 --> 00:15:54.730
A runic statue!

218
00:15:54.730 --> 00:15:56.850
Veinte Fleurs!

219
00:15:56.850 --> 00:15:58.020
Calendula!

220
00:16:10.780 --> 00:16:15.950
How long are you going to keep
protecting this withered old city?

221
00:16:17.540 --> 00:16:18.620
You don't seem...

222
00:16:20.290 --> 00:16:24.630
to have any respect for
the vestiges of our ancestors.

223
00:16:25.960 --> 00:16:28.470
I care not for the past!

224
00:16:29.470 --> 00:16:32.760
Truly the words of a fool.

225
00:16:35.060 --> 00:16:37.600
Who do you take me for?!

226
00:16:37.600 --> 00:16:39.520
Punch Mountain!

227
00:16:40.900 --> 00:16:45.940
I need to move away from the ruins
before this simpleton destroys them all!

228
00:16:57.580 --> 00:16:59.670
I chose to travel with Luffy,

229
00:16:59.670 --> 00:17:03.250
yet these ruins could hold clues
about the untold history

230
00:17:03.250 --> 00:17:04.960
lost to the world below!

231
00:17:20.690 --> 00:17:22.810
How far are you going to run?

232
00:17:54.720 --> 00:17:58.890
Have you stopped running?

233
00:17:58.890 --> 00:17:59.850
Yes.

234
00:18:00.480 --> 00:18:02.390
It's too late now.

235
00:18:03.230 --> 00:18:04.150
Too late?

236
00:18:05.650 --> 00:18:08.110
Even if you repent,
I won't forgive you!

237
00:18:10.280 --> 00:18:12.780
You won't forgive me?

238
00:18:12.780 --> 00:18:15.660
You certainly do adore
those shabby ruins.

239
00:18:15.660 --> 00:18:18.540
Especially when they don't
even belong to you...

240
00:18:18.990 --> 00:18:20.330
That's right.

241
00:18:20.330 --> 00:18:22.370
The ruins belong to no one.

242
00:18:22.790 --> 00:18:26.500
I don't feel like talking
with you anymore.

243
00:18:27.540 --> 00:18:29.170
Don't worry.

244
00:18:29.170 --> 00:18:32.130
You won't have to...

245
00:18:32.130 --> 00:18:35.930
because this is where
you get crushed to death!

246
00:18:35.930 --> 00:18:38.430
Drop Mountain!

247
00:18:38.890 --> 00:18:41.810
Now I can go all out!

248
00:18:41.810 --> 00:18:43.600
Treinta Fleurs!

249
00:18:46.690 --> 00:18:49.150
All you can do is rush
forward like a bull...

250
00:18:50.820 --> 00:18:54.070
Realize the weight of
the history you destroyed!

251
00:18:54.950 --> 00:18:55.910
Hang!

252
00:19:01.160 --> 00:19:02.580
He's so heavy!

253
00:19:17.550 --> 00:19:18.220
Take this!

254
00:19:18.220 --> 00:19:20.180
Tenfold Axe!

255
00:19:21.560 --> 00:19:23.520
Axe Mountain!

256
00:19:26.350 --> 00:19:28.110
My eyes!

257
00:19:29.860 --> 00:19:30.940
What are you–

258
00:19:30.940 --> 00:19:31.530
Huh?!

259
00:19:31.940 --> 00:19:34.820
Wait! The dials... They're backwards!

260
00:19:34.820 --> 00:19:36.570
Wait! The dials–

261
00:19:57.180 --> 00:20:00.680
Everything you destroyed was
an exquisite, priceless treasure.

262
00:20:01.300 --> 00:20:04.890
Relics so precious it's impossible
to measure their worth.

263
00:20:05.770 --> 00:20:09.900
History may repeat itself,
but people can't go back in time.

264
00:20:10.520 --> 00:20:13.570
Though you don't seem
to understand that.

265
00:20:13.570 --> 00:20:17.570
I... I understand...

266
00:20:17.570 --> 00:20:22.030
I won't ever... do it again...

267
00:20:22.030 --> 00:20:22.780
Please forgi–

268
00:20:22.780 --> 00:20:23.950
I will not.

269
00:20:27.710 --> 00:20:29.000
In that case...

270
00:20:29.000 --> 00:20:31.840
I just need to kill you!

271
00:20:36.970 --> 00:20:39.890
My fingers! Not my fingers!

272
00:20:39.890 --> 00:20:41.430
Cien Fleurs!

273
00:20:44.350 --> 00:20:45.850
Delphinium!

274
00:20:46.270 --> 00:20:49.350
What the...?! Stop!

275
00:20:50.400 --> 00:20:53.270
Wait! Where are you–

276
00:20:54.520 --> 00:20:56.990
Stop!

277
00:20:57.860 --> 00:20:59.950
It's too late for that now...

278
00:21:01.660 --> 00:21:02.530
Can't...

279
00:21:03.660 --> 00:21:04.580
breathe...

280
00:21:09.790 --> 00:21:11.040
Clutch!

281
00:21:23.470 --> 00:21:25.430
How barbaric...

282
00:21:38.940 --> 00:21:42.030
This should be the center of the city,

283
00:21:42.660 --> 00:21:45.240
but it doesn't match the map
on the monument at all.

284
00:21:46.200 --> 00:21:50.040
Did everything get scattered
from the impact of rising to the sky?

285
00:22:59.190 --> 00:23:00.820
That's strange...

286
00:23:02.110 --> 00:23:03.860
This is the City of Gold?

287
00:23:04.650 --> 00:23:08.530
As I thought, the size and topography
are completely different.

288
00:23:08.530 --> 00:23:10.290
And what's most peculiar...

289
00:23:19.840 --> 00:23:22.460
The only entrance is at the top...

290
00:23:28.050 --> 00:23:29.140
Could it be?!

291
00:23:58.380 --> 00:24:00.170
There's a way down!

292
00:24:14.180 --> 00:24:15.680
It's so vast...

293
00:24:16.180 --> 00:24:19.310
These ruins extend so much deeper!

294
00:24:19.690 --> 00:24:24.940
I thought it was strange how Blue Sea
ruins had island clouds for ground...

295
00:24:25.530 --> 00:24:29.070
The ruins above are just
the upper parts of the city,

296
00:24:29.070 --> 00:24:30.910
eaten up by island clouds...

297
00:24:31.530 --> 00:24:33.450
There's still more below!

298
00:25:02.110 --> 00:25:03.230
Light?

299
00:25:34.100 --> 00:25:38.640
Eight-hundred years ago,
the city of Shandora suddenly fell.

300
00:25:39.270 --> 00:25:41.520
It hardly seems that way, though.

301
00:25:41.520 --> 00:25:46.110
It's still so majestic and grand!

302
00:25:46.690 --> 00:25:49.110
This is Shandora, the City of Gold!

303
00:26:13.090 --> 00:26:14.470
Could it be?!

304
00:26:23.900 --> 00:26:25.360
Let me ask you a question...

305
00:26:26.310 --> 00:26:29.860
Can the untold history
be brought to light?

306
00:26:29.860 --> 00:26:32.610
Are you saying that
the poneglyphs hold that record?

307
00:26:42.750 --> 00:26:47.210
The ancient poneglyph script was
displayed right out in the open...

308
00:26:48.800 --> 00:26:55.140
Only those who created the poneglyphs
could use these symbols!

309
00:26:55.140 --> 00:26:57.760
"Hold the truth in your heart,
and speak not of it.

310
00:26:58.430 --> 00:27:01.180
We are the ones who weave history...

311
00:27:01.680 --> 00:27:04.770
with the sounding of the grand bell..."

312
00:27:06.770 --> 00:27:08.110
That's right!

313
00:27:08.610 --> 00:27:14.700
Noland's logbook did mention
a giant gold bell here...

314
00:27:16.110 --> 00:27:19.620
All of the city's writings
were burned...

315
00:27:21.740 --> 00:27:25.080
The city's history was eradicated!

316
00:27:32.380 --> 00:27:36.180
They'll manage somehow, right?

317
00:27:41.720 --> 00:27:43.730
Quit following me!

318
00:27:46.690 --> 00:27:48.650
Now it goes down?

319
00:27:50.440 --> 00:27:53.820
A poneglyph was carried into the city!

320
00:27:53.820 --> 00:27:56.320
There's no question about it!

321
00:27:56.320 --> 00:27:58.200
This city was under siege!

322
00:27:59.570 --> 00:28:01.740
Shandora, the City of Gold,

323
00:28:01.740 --> 00:28:05.580
fought and fell trying
to protect that poneglyph!

324
00:28:09.040 --> 00:28:13.500
In which case, the grand belfry
located in the center of the four altars...

325
00:28:14.260 --> 00:28:17.380
might contain the true history...

326
00:28:19.640 --> 00:28:21.970
The rio poneglyph!
